<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-07T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-07T23:00:00-05:00" n="310" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/5–854: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Thailand</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Donovan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bangkok</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-08T11:00:00+07:00">May 8,
                                    1954—11 a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2237. Re <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> telegram sent Department
                            678 repeated Bangkok 2. I convinced <persName corresp="#p_NARADHIPP1">Prince Narathip</persName>,<note n="1" xml:id="d310fn1">Also known
                                as <persName corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1">Prince Wan</persName>.</note>
                            Thai Foreign Minister, should be elected president General Assembly this
                            fall to enable both US and entire free world to benefit from his
                            election as one three chairmen at Korean phase Geneva conference and his
                            strong and valuable speeches made said conference in connection
                            unification Korea. His stand at Geneva <pb facs="0567" n="539" xml:id="pg_539"/> on question “Asia for Asians” further demonstrates
                            advantages to be gained his presidency <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. Certain this preferable in Thailand to Thailand selection
                            Security Council. Further convinced <persName corresp="#p_NARADHIPP1">Narathip</persName> should be informed promptly decision US both
                            vote for and generally support <persName corresp="#p_NARADHIPP1">Narathip</persName> for presidency <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Donovan</hi>
                                </persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>